# Clara: How the AI should work

- Map requested changes to the most relevant task(s) in `docs/TASKS.md` before coding.
- Treat `docs/DOMAIN_SCHEMAS.md` as the canonical source of truth for domain types and invariants.
- Prefer clarity over cleverness: readable, explicit code and incremental complexity.
- Keep architectural boundaries:
  - Frontend: UI states + rendering; no financial calculations outside the rules engine.
  - Backend: thin routes + validated inputs; predictable error handling.
- For UI changes, always define `loading`, `empty`, `error`, and `success` states.
- For financial logic, ensure determinism and explainability (no hidden side effects).
- If scope/acceptance criteria are missing, ask targeted clarifying questions before making broad changes.
- Include a short test/verification plan and highlight edge cases affected by the change.
